          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value, which can be used in queries wherever a single value is expected. This function is designed to determine and return the current billing period based on the input parameters provided. It is typically used in financial or subscription-based systems where billing periods need to be calculated dynamically."
        }
      ]
    },
